    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Objects in the form of a fish, designed to attract other fish for capture by the harpoon, spear, or leister of ice fishermen. Unlike a fishing lure, a fish decoy doesn't have a hook attached.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
